<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Gary Neville has highlighted England's welcome conundrum at right back after both Reece James and Tariq Lamptey gained plenty of plaudits on Monday evening.Â </p>

<p>A new-look Chelsea side were able to defeat Brighton 3-1 in their first Premier League clash of the new season, with James having crashed home an unstoppable effort from distance on the south coast.</p>

<p>Lamptey also impressed down the same flank for the hosts, leaving Neville to jokingly insist that a jibe from fellow pundit Jamie Carragher has sparked a 'phenomenon' in that position.</p>

<p>Gary Neville has hailed England's right back dilemma after Reece James' stunner at Brighton</p>

<p>Tariq Lamptey, another young English full back, also impressed for the hosts against Chelsea</p>

<p>'The performance levels and the demands that are put on the modern day full back are absolutely incredible,' Neville said. 'Not just to defend, but to deliver assists, to deliver goals, match-winning moments.Â </p>

<p>'You think of the options now that England have at full back. Reece James, Lamptey, you've got Kyle Walker, (Kieran) Trippier, Trent Alexander-Arnold is one of the best players in the world.Â </p>

<p>'He (Carragher) once said that no-one wants to grow up to be a Gary Neville! There is a lot of them, he's started a phenomenon!'Â </p>

