<p>Neville joked a jibe from Jamie Carragher sparked a 'phenomenon' for England at right back</p>

<p>As well as netting his thunderbolt, James also picked up an assist for Kurt Zouma's deflected effort and proved a nuisance at both ends of the field.</p>

<p>He made 37 appearances in all competitions last season, underlining his first-team breakthrough under Frank Lampard, and was again preferred ahead of club captain Cesar Azpilicueta against Brighton.Â </p>

<p>Lampard admitted that the starlet's piledriver had him 'off his seat'.Â </p>

<p>He said: 'We needed it, we weren't at our best in that period. Reece has got that in him, he is a player of such quality. You try and get him in areas where he can be a threat.'</p>

<p>James enjoyed a superb breakthrough last season and capped the start of the new one in style</p>

<p>James' opposite number, meanwhile, ended the last campaign in fine form and recently earned his first England U21s call-up.</p>

<p>The 19-year-old had caught the eye across Brighton's last eight matches after joining from Chelsea in January.</p>

<p>Lamptey has previously represented his nation from U18 through to U20 level and, alongside James, will harbour ambitions of breaking into the senior set-up in the future.</p>
